  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table width=85% border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0 align=center>
  <tr>
    <td bgcolor='0e024d' class='spti2'>THE DISCIPLINE OF MIGHTY STRIKE</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Class:</b>&nbsp;Warrior</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Level obtained:</b>&nbsp;54</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Duration:</b>&nbsp;10 seconds.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay:</b>&nbsp;60 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay at Level 60:</b>&nbsp;54 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b><u>Discipline Description:</u></b><P>When using this discipline all landed attacks will automatically be either Critical Hits or Crippling Blows.  This discipline lasts for 10 seconds and has a base reuse time of 60 minutes.  The reuse time for this discipline will decrease as the warrior gains additional levels.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='#000066' class='spti2'>DISCIPLINE COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>IT WOULD SEEM TO ME</span><b>, By Nallatikie nomanna</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>That if you were at haste cap, and strength cap, you couldnt gain any benefit from being beserk.  If this is true, then using this in this situation would wield the same results as letting yourself fall below 35% health. It would be true that whatever weapon that you use that does the most damage normally would be wise to use with this discipline. Although I have not seen this in use personally, the prospect of scoring crippling/criticals with every blow is immense.  Bringing down 25-35% health of a mob in 10 seconds is really quite helpful in any situation.  Too bad on the refresh time.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>WEIGHTED AXE</span><b>, By Bugguluk</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>The best idea with this discipline would be to whip out your Weighted Axe first, get 1 huge hit in, then start dual weilding.  I do this in normal fights (without the dis) and it is very effective.  So you would (potentially) get a big 400ish damage hit in, then a whole lot of 150ish hits with your faster weapons.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>CHAMPION OF XEGONY</span><b>, By Blain </b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>Well, I was in Karnors last night doing the hand/warlord room.I leveled to 54 and instructed the cleric to let me go beserk on a tough mob. I'm using Wurmslayer main hand and I was doing crits for 160 -190 all night before the discpline use. I went beserk, activated the Mightystrike on a Bodyguard and my best crip was 299 (308 actual damage dealt). One thing you had better trust your cleric. <br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>HEH</span><b>, By Muufasa</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>If you want to do a ton of dam w/ this I'd suggest using shimmering partisana and wurmslayer I can crack out around 1.5-2.5k dam depending on how many times it lands<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>54TH WARRIOR</span><b>, By Ghazaki</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>I just myself got lvl 54 and I love what this discipline has to offer. I have tested it with both 2hs and 2 1h weapons.  Results are that with 2 1h weapons I can crack out anywhere from 1k to 2k dmg (Lammy 9/19 + Silken whip of ensnaring 14/28), With my 2hander  (Soul Leech 30/45) I only do about 1k if I hit say 60% of the say 7 to 9 swings with Haste from and Ench.  My best advice is to use this with 2 fast 1h weapons and land as many hits as u can because a crip goes from anywhere from 4X to 10+X the base dmg of the weapon. <P>
Those who think that this is good with a weighted axe ,well you don't you jack about what it is being a warrior then.  The only thing a weighted axe is good for is with the dicipline where the warrior automaticaly ripostes agains all atks.  That's my 2cp about this cool lvl 54 dicipline.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
